            <strong>Question 1:</strong> What decisions has CWDS made regarding Safety and Risk Assessment tools (e.g., SDM)?  Specifically, is the Intake RFP written in such a way that:</br>
    <ul>
    		<li>1. It allows the vendor to choose what risk assessment tool will be included within the Intake digital service?</li></br>
    		<li>2. It will require the risk assessment tool to be embedded in the Intake digital service?</li></br>
    </ul>
    <strong>Response:</strong> The Child Welfare Directors have agreed to use the SDM assessment tool statewide. While the technical solutions for integrating SDM and CWS-NS have not yet been determined, the goal is to provide a seamless solution with bi-directional data exchange between the two.</br></br>
    
    <strong>Question 2:</strong> Will tracking of differential response be part of NS?</br>
    <strong>Response:</strong> To date, all of the primary emergency response social worker activities are being identified as features for the Intake digital service.  Differential response has been identified as one feature; however, no decision has been made as to whether it will be contained in the initial release or a subsequent release.  These decisions will be made as we move through the sprints, work with the vendor, and prioritize the features.
    
