    		   <strong>Question 1:</strong> During the timeframe when both the current CWS/CMS and the new Intake digital service will be in operation, will users be able to access both systems using a single sign-on?</br>
    
    <strong>Response:</strong> The goal is to allow users to login to CWS/CMS (legacy) and CWS-NS (new) applications using the same ID and password (their current CWS/CMS credentials), but this may require that users login separately to each application.</br></br>
    
    <strong>Question 2:</strong> Will Business Objects be updated as CWS-NS is updated?</br>
    <strong>Response:</strong> Business Objects will continue to be available while New System is in development.  The New System team is evaluating options to include New System data elements in Business Objects, and is researching long term alternatives with the goal of identifying a more modern, easy to use solution for reporting.</br></br>
    
    <strong>Question 3:</strong> How will the help desk work with multiple vendors (dedicated and co-existent counties)?</br>
    <strong>Response:</strong> Our goal is to provide stakeholders with a single help desk contact to address system needs and issues.</br></br>
    
